00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:26.880
And the other thing I think that really contributes to this is, um, you all, you

00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:31.160
almost always are ending up collaborating across functions.

00:33:31.160 --> 00:33:36.000
So most typically, like you are needing you, if you're a more statistical person,

00:33:36.119 --> 00:33:39.479
you are now needing to collaborate with someone who's a more OPSI person.

00:33:39.839 --> 00:33:42.160
And people work in different ways.

00:33:42.160 --> 00:33:44.160
Teams, um, don't sit together.

00:33:44.160 --> 00:33:48.920
It's like, like, like people end up with like, Oh, that will never work.

00:33:48.959 --> 00:33:50.599
You know, like that will never work because of X.

00:33:50.599 --> 00:33:54.839
And like, what, like, what can both sides do to actually make

00:33:54.839 --> 00:33:56.040
something work if it needs to happen?

00:33:56.040 --> 00:34:00.079
So I think those are like the real reasons why this kind of thing happens.

